cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with cake-cutting protocols, which are a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS). The concept of envy-freeness is a central theme in the paper, which is also a topic of interest in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a new protocol, which involves proportional division of the cake, and analyzes its properties, which is a common approach in mechanism design (cs.MA) and computational social choice (cs.LG).
